default              
defaultUnder subsection 7A(1) TPDA, a manufacturer must, so far as is reasonably practicable, avoid:
default              
default(a) supplying cigarettes or hand-rolling tobacco to persons who are likely to smuggle them into the UK;
default              
default(b) supplying cigarettes or hand-rolling tobacco in circumstances where the nature of the supply makes it likely that they will be resupplied to persons who are likely to smuggle them into the UK; or
default              
default(c) otherwise facilitating the smuggling into the UK of cigarettes or hand-rolling tobacco.
default              
default"Smuggling" is defined at subsection 7A(3) TPDA as importing into the UK without payment of the requisite duty.
